## üéì Overview

My research integrates **advanced statistical modeling** and **machine learning** to address complex problems in **precision medicine**, **epidemiology**, **ecology**, and **environmental science**.  
I develop interpretable **Bayesian and probabilistic frameworks** for heterogeneous, high-dimensional, and bounded data ‚Äî always seeking a balance between **methodological innovation** and **real-world impact**.  

<!-- Beyond scientific contributions, I am deeply committed to **Science Communication and Public Engagement**, promoting accessibility and trust in research, particularly within **Latin American contexts** where science often faces undervaluation.   -->

---

## üî¨ Predicting Individual Treatment Effects (PITE) ‚Äî *Precision Medicine and Clinical Trials*

Current research focuses on **Bayesian learning** and **hybrid AI** to predict individualized treatment responses, advancing personalized healthcare and clinical decision-making.

- **(2025)** *A Bayesian Additive Regression Trees Model for Zero and One Inflated Data*  
  Development of a flexible Bayesian framework for *Predicting Individual Treatment Effects (PITE)* in alcohol use disorder trials.  
  [Preprint ‚Üí](https://arxiv.org/html/2507.19848v1)

- **(2025)** *Hybrid AI Methods for Feature Selection in Personalized Treatment Effect Prediction*  
  Integration of meta-heuristic optimization and explainable AI for PITE modeling.  
  [WiDS 2025 ‚Üí](https://pchiroque.github.io/files/WIDS_2025.pdf)

- **(2025)** *Bayesian Approaches to Predicting Individual Treatment Effects in Precision Medicine*  
  Evaluation of Bayesian paradigms in individualized inference.  
  [BAYSM 2025 ‚Üí](https://pchiroque.github.io/files/BAYSM2025.pdf)

- **(2024)** *Regression-Based Trees for Outcomes with Closed Boundary Domains*  
  Machine learning for constrained outcomes in biomedical research.  
  [WiDS 2024 ‚Üí](https://pchiroque.github.io/files/WIDS_poster_14May24_P.pdf)

- **(2024)** *Comparing Modern Machine Learning Methods for Predicting Individual Treatment Effects*  
  Benchmark study evaluating Bayesian and frequentist approaches in PITE context.  
  [ISCB 2024 ‚Üí](https://pchiroque.github.io/files/ISCB24724.pdf)

