## üìä Advanced Statistical Modeling and Machine Learning

Applied research spanning **ecology**, **environmental monitoring**, and **risk modeling**, with emphasis on **Bayesian inference**, **hierarchical models**, and **multivariate probabilistic analysis**.

- **(2023)** *Probabilistic Models and Machine Learning for Biomass and LAI Prediction*  
  Integration of multispectral‚ÄìLiDAR UAV data for environmental monitoring.  
  [Abstract ‚Üí](https://www.stat.purdue.edu/conferences/agstats2023/documents/Program%20Booklet%202023%20BAC11.pdf)

- **(2022)** *Mapping Leaf Area Index of Chestnut Trees Using UAV-Based Multispectral Data*  
  Remote sensing and predictive modeling of forest structure.  
  [Journal Paper ‚Üí](https://doi.org/10.3390/drones6120422)

- **(2021)** *Community Surveillance of COVID-19 Using Wastewater Data*  
  Bayesian hierarchical modeling for epidemic monitoring.  
  *Collaboration with T. Marques and M. Vieira.*

- **(2021)** *Coral Growth Bands and Trace Elements after the Fund√£o Dam Collapse*  
  Environmental reconstruction via hierarchical Bayesian inference.  
  [Science of the Total Environment ‚Üí](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.scitotenv.2021.150880)

- **(2021)** *Decadal Dynamics of Southwestern Atlantic Turbid Reefs*  
  Multivariate modeling of long-term ecological data.  
  [PLOS ONE ‚Üí](https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0247111)

- **(2020)** *Tropical Rhodolith Beds as Major Reef Fish Habitats*  
  Multilevel ecological modeling of biodiversity.  
  [Scientific Reports ‚Üí](https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-020-80574-w)

