## üåç Epidemiology and Public Health ‚Äî *Science Communication and Social Impact*

During the COVID-19 pandemic, I contributed to **A√ß√£o Covid19**, a volunteer scientific network aimed at **translating complex data into accessible language**, ensuring reliable, transparent information for the community.

- **(2020)** *COVID-19 Waves: Accumulative Mortality and Epidemic Dynamics*  
Time-series analysis of mortality data to identify temporal trends and epidemic dynamics.  
  [Tohoku Journal of Experimental Medicine ‚Üí](https://doi.org/10.1620/tjem.251.47)

- **(2023)** *COVID-19 Protection Index (CPI)*  
  Geospatial approach to identify regional vulnerabilities in Brazil.  
  [Springer Chapter ‚Üí](https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-24541-1_21)

- **(2020)** *COVID-19 Vulnerability Mapping*  
  Geostatistical modeling and public dissemination of epidemiological data.  
  [Project ‚Üí](https://www.youtube.com/c/A%C3%A7%C3%A3oCovid19)

- **(2021)** *Vaccination Process and Epidemiological Surveillance in Brazil*  
  Predictive analysis of vaccination rollout and transmission dynamics.  
  [Project Report ‚Üí](files/R0_acao_covid.pdf)

- **(2020)** *Confirmed COVID-19 Cases in Peru by District*  
  Early-stage outbreak modeling and data visualization.  
  [Publication ‚Üí](https://doi.org/10.1620/tjem.251.47)

